p;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; a. Basic Home Safety (JCAHO:S1.1.1.1.1)                .form-group.col-md-12.row                    p.card-text.text-dark                        | &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; b. The safe and appropriate use of medical equipment (JCAHO:S1.1.1.1.1.1)                .form-group.col-md-12.row                    p.card-text.text-dark                        | &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; c. The storage handling, delivery and access to supplies, medical gasses, and drugs with specific reference, as appropriate to chemotherapeutic agents, controlled substances, parenteral and enteral nutrition solutions needles. ( JCAHO:S1.1.1.1.1.4 )                .form-group.col-md-12.row                    p.card-text.text-dark                        | &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; d. The identification, handling. and disposal of hazardous materials and wasTes in a safe and sanitary manner, and in accordance wiTh applicable law and regulations (JCAHO:Sl.l.l.l.l.4)                .form-group.col-md-12.row                    p.card-text.text-dark                        | &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; e. The patient's knowledge and performance of safety procedures is monitored on an ongoing basis through the plan of treatment process. appropriate instruction in provided as deficiencies are identified (JCAHO:S1.1.4)                .form-group.col-md-12.row                    p.card-text.text-dark                        | &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; f. The staff knowledge and performance of the safe and appropriate use of equipment related to the care services provided are monitored on an ongoing basis appropriate related to the care services provided are monitored on an ongoing basis appropriate instruction is provided (JCAHO:S1.1.4)                .form-group.col-md-12.row                    p.card-text.text-dark                 